description: Borrowing from New Latin vāgīnālis, from vāgīna (“a covering, sheath; the vagina”) +‎ -ālis (“-al”, adjectival suffix); equivalent to vagina +‎ -al.

entries.meaning: (relational) Of, relating to, or affecting the vagina.
examples: You may have a vaginal birth, C-section or surrogacy; it's up to you.

entries.meaning: (anatomy, relational) Of or relating to a theca.
